Instruction: Electrically isolate Control Module 6 and the remainder of the chain by disconnecting the cables between Modules 5 and 6. With the battery in and all switches ON, first measure voltage across the two output terminals of Module 5 (module-side, not the loose cables). Then measure voltage across the two input terminals of Module 6 (module-side). Finally, with Module 6 still disconnected from the rest, measure continuity (ohms) between its input + and input − to check for an internal short. Record whether Module 5 still has ~12 V across its output pair and whether Module 6 input shows an unexpected low resistance/short.
