2026-04-21 01:27:18 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=["Internal wiring / PCB trace between Control Input Cable (+) 6 port 'n' and Control Switch 6 (open / not bonded)"] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that in Control Module 6 the individual elements (input + terminal hardware, switch, and output + terminal hardware) each have nominal continuity locally, but one end of the input + conductor (port ‘n’) is floating and NOT actually connected to the switch node that should carry the series 12 V through the module. With the module in‑circuit, +12 V appears at the input (+) terminal, while the output (+) terminal remains at 0 V; resistance between input (+) and output (+) is ~7×10¹¹ Ω. This is consistent with an open circuit specifically in the short link (PCB trace/jumper or internal wiring) that should bond Control Input Cable (+) 6 port ‘n’ to the switch common. The missing indicator LED/resistor simply means the parallel indicator branch is absent; it does not explain the open series path. Repairing or re‑establishing the electrical connection between port ‘n’ of the input (+) and the switch common pad should restore continuity of the positive line past Module 6 and allow power to reach Modules 7–8 and the load.'
